    <h1>Full-Bleed Sections</h1>
    <p>As you can see, the backgrounds of sections below extend to the ends of the screen. This is done by simply adding a <code>div</code> with class <code>.full-bleed</code> around a <code>.container</code> element. Otherwise, you follow the rules with wrapping things inside the appropriate grid wrappers, such as <code>.full-width</code> and <code>.row></code>, etc.</p>
    <p>All types of gridded content (shown below) can be used inside of full-bleed areas without any tweaks needed.</p>
  </div> <!-- end:. content -->

